-- PList (list-literal pattern): `[a, b, c]` matches a 3-element list, binding
-- `a`=1, `b`=2, `c`=3.  The decision tree (canonPat) normalises [a,b,c] to
-- PCons/Nil form; bindPattern's new PList arm decomposes the raw PList.
-- Reduces to 1 + 2 + 3 = 6.
main = match [1, 2, 3]
  [a, b, c] => a + b + c
  _ => 0
